We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to:
Require the Collectors/Designated Collectors to immediately remit/deposit the unremitted prior years’ collections; otherwise, initiate disciplinary action;
Require all Accountable Officers to remit daily and intact all current collections within the day or the next banking day;
Require the Cashier to deposit immediately the cash remitted by the Liquidating Officer;
Require the Cashier to maintain a record book for each Collector/Designated Collector to record under or over remittance found after review of their respective Report of Collections and Deposits (RCDs);
Prioritize the full integration of the Enhanced Tax Revenue Assessment and Collection System (ETRACS) to cover the whole process of collection from the issuance of Accountable Forms to Deposit of Collection and automatic generation of reports;
Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to give “Unsatisfactory Rating” to those errant Collectors and disqualify them from receiving Performance Bonus;
Require the Municipal Treasurer to stop issuing new stubs of Official Receipts to Collectors unless all previously issued receipts are accounted/returned with cash collections duly remitted to the Liquidating Officer; and
Discuss with the MTO and Accounting Office the adequacy of staff to handle collections and review of reports.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to require:
The coordination between the Municipal Accountant and the GSO to follow prescribed inventory procedures in maintaining a perpetual inventory method in the recording of all Inventory Accounts;
The Municipal Accountant and GSO to maintain the prescribed ledger cards and stock cards, respectively, for each type of Inventory, keep track of the actual Supplies Inventory on hand and reconcile the balances of the two inventory records;
The Internal Auditor to evaluate and monitor internal controls in relation to request and issuance of Inventories; and
The Municipal Accountant to prepare adjusting entries to transfer the Inventory accounts to the correct expense accounts and provide this audit team a copy of the JEV.

The SWM Board to strictly monitor the sale of recyclable materials to junk shops and accordingly issue official receipts for said collections;

Improve the Manocmanoc MRF by building structures to ensure that collected segregated waste remain segregated upon delivery to the MRF;

Exert regular and consistent effort in the conduct of IEC programs at community-level to encourage cooperation and awareness of all its constituents; and

Exert effort in the implementation of projects and programs that are aimed to reduce residual waste of the Municipality.

Require the Project Engineers to prepare the ABCs in accordance with the DPWH DO 197 with the computations duly reviewed and checked; 

Settle the discrepancy of overestimated project cost (of the two classroom school building) with the Contractor and to require the Contractor to refund and/or deduct the corresponding excess amount from its remaining claims from the LGU, otherwise a Notice of Disallowance will be issued;

Require the Project Engineers to strictly monitor, evaluate, and validate all project accomplishments to ensure that the projects are on schedule and are performed in accordance with the approved POWs, and issues and lapses thereof are addressed immediately;

Require the Municipal Engineer to demand from the Oval Track Contractor immediate delivery of materials and completion of scope of works according to specifications, otherwise, enforce rights as provided for in Section 62 Rule XIX of the R-IRR of RA 9184;

Take appropriate action to collect the liquidated damages from the Contractor (Oval Track) for the delays incurred.    If circumstances warrant, initiate termination of Contract with the assistance of the LGU’s Legal Counsel in accordance with GPPB Circular No. 03-2019 dated 8 March 2019 and Annex I of the Revised IRR of RA 9184;

Validate the reasons of the contractor in requesting time extension and determine if such is based on meritorious ground and is filed before the expiry of the original completion date;

Ensure that communications from Contractor be stamped received by the LGU’s authorized representative and dated in the same way that outgoing communications of the LGU be duly received and dated;

Require the Engineering Office to submit Variation Orders for the Construction of Classroom supported with technical specifications and detailed cost breakdown;

Require the Project Engineers to include as a requirement for payment on-site and laboratory tests to ensure that embedded items, embankment, subbase and base course, PCCP, etc.  conforms with quality standards; 

Include as a requirement for final billing settlement of water and electric usage from the recipient schools. Advise Contractors to coordinate with the DepEd Aklan Cash Unit for the mode of payment and issuance of Official Receipt; and

Require the Project Engineers to observe proper labeling of projects to avoid confusion and to enable the accounting and the supply units to properly record the assets with its correct description.

Prepare the ABCs in accordance with the DPWH DO 197 with the computations duly reviewed and checked; 

Settle the discrepancy of overestimated project cost with the Contractor and to require the Contractor to refund and/or deduct the corresponding excess amount from its remaining claims from the LGU, otherwise a Notice of Disallowance will be issued;

Substantiate/submit quantity take off and details of the P1,000,000.00 water reservoir;

Explain the varying estimates for the estimated direct costs of project billboards. Have a standard detailed estimate for direct cost, design/plans and specifications for the project billboards considering the location of the project;

Strictly monitor, evaluate, and validate all project accomplishments to ensure that the projects are on schedule and are performed in accordance with the approved POWs, and issues and lapses thereof are addressed immediately;

Require the Contractor to accomplish the unperformed scope of works, specifically the application of Reflectorized Thermo Plastic Pavement Marking and asphalt sealant for the Sambiray Road Concreting and installation of the remaining 125 service connections of the Naasug Water System and to submit accomplishment/compliance report with pictures at the Office of the Auditor;

Require the Contractor to refund the excess amount paid for billboards after deducting the actual cost thereof from the cost per contract; otherwise a Notice of Disallowance will be issued;

Demand from the Contractor of Tabon Port Development and Centralized Operation Center-Phase 1 at Caticlan immediate completion of the remaining scope of works according to specifications, otherwise, enforce rights as provided for in Section 62 Rule XIX of the R-IRR of RA 9184;

Take appropriate action to collect the liquidated damages from the same Contractor for the delays incurred.    If circumstances warrant, initiate termination of Contract with the assistance of the LGU’s Legal Counsel in accordance with GPPB Circular No. 03-2019 dated 8 March 2019 and Annex I of the Revised IRR of RA 9184;

Require Contractors that for ongoing and future contracts, request for time extension (if any) must be supported with Performance Security to cover approved contract time extensions;

Validate the reasons of the contractor and determine if such is based on meritorious ground and is filed before the expiry of the original completion date, otherwise concerned personnel of the LGU will be held liable for the corresponding Liquidated Damages;

Ensure that the communications between the LGU and the Contractor be stamped received and dated by its respective authorized personnel;

Require the Contractor of on-going and future projects to submit supporting documents for the payment of PPEs such as Official Receipts, pictures, distribution list signed by laborers, otherwise payment thereof may be suspended in audit; and

Report unused construction materials and forms/scaffoldings and turn-over the same to the General Services Office of the Municipality in accordance with Item 3.1 of COA Circular No. 82-92-H dated October 17, 1982.

Ensure that only necessary expenditures are incurred, observe prudence and fiscal restraint in utilizing government funds which are intended for public purpose and strictly adhere to the provisions of COA Circular No. 2012-003 dated October 29, 2012 to avoid incurrence of irregular, unnecessary, excessive, extravagant and unconscionable expenditures;

Formulate guidelines to set the parameters and regulate the granting of load allowance; and

Require the Accounting Unit to review the monthly billing statement and to reimburse only the amount whichever is less of the actual amount in the monthly billing statement or the ceiling/allowable amount, exclude from payment the following: a) data booster add-ons; b) subscription on sites; c) reconnection fees and other administrative fees; d) roaming texts, data and call charges (unless supported with proof that the same was used for official purposes); and e) monthly amortizations for device.

The LDRRMC prepare and submit a revised LDRRMFIP as basis for any revision to the PPAs to be charged to the LDRRMF and is duly supported by an approved revised AIP;

The LDRRMC make sure that revised LDRRMFIP is consistent with any supplemental budget and with all other related reports such as the Monthly Utilization Report and SAAOB; and

The LDRRMC exert effort in implementing programs and activities identified in the LDRRMFIP provided that the PPAs identified are indeed chargeable to the LDRRMF.

The SWM Board to strictly monitor the sale of recyclable materials to junk shops and accordingly issue official receipts for said collections;

Improve the Manocmanoc MRF by building structures to ensure that collected segregated waste remain segregated upon delivery to the MRF;

Exert regular and consistent effort in the conduct of IEC programs at community-level to encourage cooperation and awareness of all its constituents; and

Exert effort in the implementation of projects and programs that are aimed to reduce residual waste of the Municipality.

