We recommended and the Management agreed to the following:
The LDRRMC prepare and submit a revised LDRRMFIP as basis for any revision to the PPAs to be charged to the LDRRMF and is duly supported by an approved revised AIP;
The LDRRMC make sure that revised LDRRMFIP is consistent with any supplemental budget and with all other related reports such as the Monthly Utilization Report and SAAOB;
The LDRRMC stop the utilization of the LDRRMF for projects and activities not included in the LDRRMFIP and AIP;
The LDRRMC exert effort in implementing programs and activities identified in the LDRRMFIP provided that the PPAs identified are indeed chargeable to the LDRRMF;
The LDRRMC and Municipal Budget Officer ensure that the LDRRMF be strictly utilized exclusively for expenditures related to disaster prevention and mitigation, preparedness, response and rehabilitation, and recovery only; and
The Municipal Accountant prepare Adjusting Journal Entries to correct the charging of the expenditures including those from the Accounts Payable account.

The Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant to analyze, review, reconcile and monitor all booked liability accounts;

Adjust the books to ensure that only obligations with valid claims remain in the books;

Maintain and update the subsidiary ledgers and schedules regularly complete with necessary details on the accounts; and

Reconcile   balances with the General Ledger.

The Municipal Mayor must give paramount importance to the full integration of e-collection system to cover the whole process of collection from the issuance of Accountable Forms to Deposit of Collection and automatic generation of reports;

The Municipal Treasurer may consider giving “Unsatisfactory Rating” to those errant Collectors;

The Municipality to prioritize the filling up of vacant positions for the MTO should funds be available; and

The Municipality to create position for Information Technology Officer/Programmer to manage software programs of the Municipality.

The Municipal Mayor instruct the Municipal Accountant and other concerned officials to analyze, trace records and determine the details of the unremitted amounts and cause its immediate remittance to the PHIC and/or make the necessary adjustments in the Municipality’s books of accounts, as the case maybe;

Remit the full amount of contributions withheld from the salaries of the LGU personnel on the month following the month in which withholding was made to avoid any variances, and to hold the person/s responsible for the delayed remittances to personally answer for the penalties and surcharges that may be imposed by the PHIC.

Recheck/review the accuracy of the total amount of contributions and the amount to be remitted to PHIC every month before making any remittances to avoid over and/or underpayment.

The Municipal Accountant prepare adjusting entries to correct the Trust Liabilities – DRRM account;

Henceforth, prepare and submit the monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF on or before the 15th day after the end of each month; and 

Submit revised subsidiary ledgers classified in accordance with the requirements of Section 5.1.12 of COA Circular No. 2012-002.

The Municipal Accountant make sure that all travel claims are duly supported by complete supporting documents as provided by pertinent laws and regulations;

The Municipal Mayor should only issue the certification of absolute necessity when the assigned task of the officials and employees necessitates the availment of actual accommodation expenses that exceed the accommodation component of the DTE;

Avoid going through travel agencies in booking flights and accommodations; and

Stop the use of CENRR for payment to establishments and PUVs that are mandated by law to issue receipts.

The Local Chief Executive (LCE) require the LDRRM Council to prepare and submit the Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Investment Plan (LDRRMIP) indicating under a separate caption, the list of projects and activities charged to the unexpended LDRRMF of previous years for ease of monitoring of project implementation and evaluation;

Justify the use of the LDRRMF for unnecessary expenditures as listed in Appendix D of this memorandum; and

The Municipal Accountant prepare Adjusting Journal Entries to correct the charging of the expenditures including those from the Accounts Payable account.

The Municipal Mayor to create a committee to review its organizational structure to evaluate the manpower needs of all departments and divisions to ensure optimum delivery of service to its constituent;

Vacant regular positions should be filled up first and redundant or unnecessary job orders such as those that duplicate the work of regular employees should be limited;

The Committee shall review, recommend revisions if warranted, and recommend for approval the proposed Guidelines in the Hiring of JO Personnel; and

Once approved, adjust the rates of JOs to on the basis of their qualifications, nature of work/designation, length of service/employment, and etc. as may be prescribed in the guidelines.

Ensure that the development projects to be funded out of the 20% DF are well-planned, procurement-and implementation-ready to achieve its full implementation according to its approved Annual Investment Plan;

The Municipal Engineer ensure that the computation for Approved Budget for the Contract (ABC) be supported with Quantity Take Off, otherwise the transaction/s will be suspended in audit;

The Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) Secretariat make certain that NTPs must be duly received, signed and dated by the Contractor or his authorized representative; and

Encourage residents of Brgy. Napaan and nearby barangays to avail the water services provided by the local water district to maximize the utilization of Napaan Water System and to secure the provision of clean and safe drinking water.

