We recommended and the Management agreed that:
The Municipal Mayor must give paramount importance to the full integration of e-collection system to cover the whole process of collection from the issuance of Accountable Forms to Deposit of Collection and automatic generation of reports;
The Municipal Mayor to require all Accountable Officers to remit daily and intact all collections within the day or within the next banking day, otherwise, impose disciplinary action if warranted;
The Municipal Treasurer may consider giving “Unsatisfactory Rating” to those errant Collectors;
The Liquidating Officer to continue the good practice of the immediate turn-over of cash received from collectors to the Cashier with the corresponding RCD. However, to comply with Section 31 (b), Chapter 3, Volume I of the MNGAS for LGUs, it is recommended that it must be the Liquidating Officer who shall perform the verification of ORs, amount collected, and the RCDs received from Collectors before transmitting the same to the Cashier. Discrepancies noted must be officially communicated and duly received by the concerned collector/s;
Collectors to fill out RCDs according to the instructions in Appendix 41, Volume II of the MNGAS for LGU. See sample filled-out RCD attached (Appendix J).
The Municipal Accountant, the Municipal Treasurer and the Cashier II to reconcile records, deposit undeposited cash balance, and record adjustments in the corresponding books/report;
The Collectors to prepare and issue the official receipts pursuant to Section 73, of GAAM, Volume I;
The Municipal Treasurer to advise Collectors to cancel issued ORs with significant alterations in amounts and figures;
The Municipality to prioritize the filling up of vacant positions for the MTO should funds be available; and
The Municipality to create position for Information Technology Officer/Programmer to manage software programs of the Municipality.

It was recommended and the Management agreed that:
The Municipal Assessor furnish the Municipal Treasurer on or before the 31st day of December of each year, an assessment roll as required by Sections 205 and 248 of RA 7160;
The Municipal Treasurer prepare a duly certified list showing the name of the taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year and submit the same to the Municipal Accountant as basis in setting up the beginning balance of RPT/SET Receivable in the books of accounts;
The Office of the Municipal Treasurer strengthen the internal control of the ETRACS system and undertake regular updating of the list of delinquent taxpayers to avoid erroneous/incorrect information relative thereto; and
The Municipal Treasurer’s Office intensify collections of realty taxes to attain higher collection efficiency.

